fields.name: Country
fields.description: Country is used for areas included (or previously included) in ISO 3166-1, e.g. United States.

fields.name: Subdivision
fields.description: Subdivision is used for the main administrative divisions of a country, e.g. California, Ontario, Okinawa. These are considered when displaying the parent areas for a given area.

fields.name: City
fields.description: City is used for settlements of any size, including towns and villages.

fields.name: Municipality
fields.description: Municipality is used for small administrative divisions which, for urban municipalities, often contain a single city and a few surrounding villages. Rural municipalities typically group several villages together.

fields.name: District
fields.description: District is used for a division of a large city, e.g. Queens.

fields.name: Island
fields.description: Island is used for islands and atolls which don't form subdivisions of their own, e.g. Skye. These are not considered when displaying the parent areas for a given area.

fields.name: County
fields.description: County is used for smaller administrative divisions of a country which are not the main administrative divisions but are also not municipalities, e.g. counties in the USA. These are not considered when displaying the parent areas for a given area.
